Capture cross section was obtained by combination
of three independent experiments/measurements
1. Measurement with a thick sample to obtain a good
statistics of capture gamma-rays
2. Measurement with a thin sample inside a 4pi
PPAC counter to measure gamma-rays associated
with fission
3. Measurements of the neutron scattering background
using a 208Pb sample
Overall fission gamma-ray spectrum obtained in
coincidence with PPAC was normalized to thick target
data in high gamma multiplicity region M>6, where
only gamma-rays associated with fission are emitted.
Thick target events with gamma multiplicity between 3
and 5 and the total gamma energy between 5.7 and
6.7 MeV were selected as capture events, and the
remaining portion fission gamma-rays was subtracted
by using the PPAC data normalized to the thick target
data.
4pi highly segmented highly efficient gamma-ray
calorimeter DANCE (inner radius of 17 cm) which
consists of 160 BaF2 scintillation crystals (15 cm
long) having the same solid-angle coverage.
To detect fission fragments and tag the
gamma-rays from fission.
